      "phase_a_text": "## The Text\n\n[Pericope: Acts 14:1-7 · source: NA28]\n\n**Original Greek (NA28)**\nοἱ δὲ ἀπειθήσαντες Ἰουδαῖοι ἐπήγειραν καὶ ἐκάκωσαν τὰς ψυχὰς τῶν ἐθνῶν κατὰ τῶν ἀδελφῶν.\n\n*Interlinear: 7 columns × 11 rows = 77 cells.*\n| # | Greek | Translit. | Strong's | Lemma | Parsing | Literal Gloss |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | οἱ | hoi | G3588 | ὁ | Art-NPM | the |\n| 2 | δὲ | de | G1161 | δέ | Conj | but / and |\n| 3 | ἀπειθήσαντες | apeithēsantes | G544 | ἀπειθέω | V-AAP-NPM | having disobeyed / disbelieved |\n| 4 | Ἰουδαῖοι | Ioudaioi | G2453 | Ἰουδαῖος | A-NPM | Jews |\n| 5 | ἐπήγειραν | epēgeiran | G1892 | ἐπεγείρω | V-AAI-3P | they stirred up / incited |\n| 6 | καὶ | kai | G2532 | καί | Conj | and |\n| 7 | ἐκάκωσαν | ekakōsan | G2559 | κακόω | V-AAI-3P | they made evil / poisoned / embittered |\n| 8 | τὰς | tas | G3588 | ὁ | Art-APF | the |\n| 9 | ψυχὰς | psychas | G5590 | ψυχή | N-APF | souls / minds / inner lives |\n| 10 | τῶν | tōn | G3588 | ὁ | Art-GPN | of the |\n| 11 | ἐθνῶν | ethnōn | G1484 | ἔθνος | N-GPN | Gentiles / nations |\n| 12 | κατὰ | kata | G2596 | κατά | Prep | against (+gen) |\n| 13 | τῶν | tōn | G3588 | ὁ | Art-GPM | the |\n| 14 | ἀδελφῶν | adelphōn | G80 | ἀδελφός | N-GPM | brothers |\n\n*(Note: The interlinear table has been expanded to 14 rows to correctly parse each word, resulting in 98 cells. The pre-emit declaration is adjusted accordingly.)*\n\n*Interlinear: 7 columns × 14 rows = 98 cells.*\n| # | Greek | Translit. | Strong's | Lemma | Parsing | Literal Gloss |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | οἱ | hoi | G3588 | ὁ | Art-NPM | the |\n| 2 | δὲ | de | G1161 | δέ | Conj | but / and |\n| 3 | ἀπειθήσαντες | apeithēsantes | G544 | ἀπειθέω | V-AAP-NPM | having disobeyed / disbelieved |\n| 4 | Ἰουδαῖοι | Ioudaioi | G2453 | Ἰουδαῖος | A-NPM | Jews |\n| 5 | ἐπήγειραν | epēgeiran | G1892 | ἐπεγείρω | V-AAI-3P | they stirred up / incited |\n| 6 | καὶ | kai | G2532 | καί | Conj | and |\n| 7 | ἐκάκωσαν | ekakōsan | G2559 | κακόω | V-AAI-3P | they made evil / poisoned / embittered |\n| 8 | τὰς | tas | G3588 | ὁ | Art-APF | the |\n| 9 | ψυχὰς | psychas | G5590 | ψυχή | N-APF | souls / minds / inner lives |\n| 10 | τῶν | tōn | G3588 | ὁ | Art-GPN | of the |\n| 11 | ἐθνῶν | ethnōn | G1484 | ἔθνος | N-GPN | Gentiles / nations |\n| 12 | κατὰ | kata | G2596 | κατά | Prep | against (+gen) |\n| 13 | τῶν | tōn | G3588 | ὁ | Art-GPM | the |\n| 14 | ἀδελφῶν | adelphōn | G80 | ἀδελφός | N-GPM | brothers |\n\n**Faithful Direct Translation**\nBut the disbelieving Jews stirred up and poisoned the souls of the Gentiles against the brothers.\n\n**Standalone English Translation**\nBut the Jews who refused to believe stirred up the Gentiles and poisoned their minds against the believers.\n\n**Amplified Narrative Translation**\nBut the Jews who willfully disobeyed [the gospel message] incited the Gentiles and maliciously corrupted their inner disposition [lit. their souls], turning them against the brothers [in Christ].\n",
