 angels, demons, and the spiritual realm\"):</strong> While the agents are human, the strategy of slander and mind-poisoning is characteristic of Satan, \"the father of lies\" (John 8:44) and the \"accuser of the brothers\" (Rev 12:10).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Christ-Centered Hermeneutic Verification:</strong> This passage points to Christ by confirming His predictions of persecution (John 15:20, \"If they persecuted me, they will also persecute you\") and by demonstrating the very darkness that He came to overcome. The apostles' perseverance in the face of this hostility is a direct reflection of Christ's own steadfastness on His way to the cross.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>",
