        "cover_art_prompts": "## Cover Art Prompts\n```nano-banana-1\nAnchor: V1 lines 1-2 — \"A long time they remained / His truth they explained\"\nA cinematic still of two robed figures from behind, standing firm before the entrance of an ancient Greco-Roman synagogue. Dust motes hang in the air, illuminated by a single shaft of intense sunlight. The mood is one of quiet, determined persistence against unseen opposition. Sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre palette. Photorealistic, shot on 35mm film, shallow depth of field.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-2\nAnchor: Chorus lines 1, 3 — \"He bears witness to the Word / The Word of all His grace\"\nAn ancient, open scroll resting on a rustic wooden lectern. A powerful, divine light emanates from the Hebrew text itself, casting long, dramatic shadows across the room. The image captures the idea that the Word itself is alive and powerful. Sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre palette. Cinematic still, volumetric light, anamorphic lens.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-3\nAnchor: V2 lines 3-4 — \"Rely on Him alone / To make His power known\"\nA close-up shot focusing on a pair of rough, calloused hands opened in a gesture of prayer and reliance. Above the hands, out of focus, a subtle shimmer of light suggests divine power being received, not generated. The focus is on dependency and trust. Sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre palette. Photorealistic, natural light, macro detail.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-4\nAnchor: Bridge lines 1-2 — \"Through these hands, O Lord, now move / Your faithfulness please prove\"\nA dynamic shot of two hands extended over a blurry crowd of indistinct figures. A soft, golden energy flows visibly from a point above the frame, through the hands, and towards the people below. This visualizes the apostles as conduits of divine power. Sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre palette. Cinematic still, motion blur, golden hour.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-5\nAnchor: Outro lines 1-2 — \"By signs their hands had shown / His grace was truly known\"\nA symbolic image of a clay oil lamp, freshly lit, sitting on a rough stone floor. Its warm light pushes back a deep, encroaching darkness, representing the grace of God being made known in a hostile world. The focus is on the small, potent light against the vast dark. Sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre palette. High-contrast chiaroscuro, shot on 35mm film.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-title\nAnchor: Title — \"The Word of His Grace\"\nA powerful, central image of an ancient scroll, glowing with an inner light, positioned at the center of the frame. From the scroll, ripples of light expand outwards, subtly transforming the dusty, ochre ground into something more vibrant and alive. This represents the Word of Grace bringing life and confirmation. Sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre palette. Cinematic still, ultra-high-resolution, dramatic lighting.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-horizon\nAnchor: Christo-telic Horizon — The ascended Christ empowering His church.\nA symbolic, wide-angle cinematic still from a low angle, looking up past a simple shepherd's staff and an open scroll resting on a rock. In the sky above, not as a person but as a brilliant convergence of light, is a throne-like formation in the clouds, from which rays of power descend toward the viewer's position. This represents the ascended Lord empowering the mission. Sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre palette.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n",
