        "cover_art_prompts": "## Cover Art Prompts\n\n```nano-banana-1\nAnchor: V1 lines 1-2 — \"The word of grace was preached / With signs for all to see\"\nA cinematic still of two men in simple, travel-worn 1st-century robes speaking to a small crowd in the dusty square of an ancient Anatolian city. A shaft of golden-hour light breaks through the clouds, illuminating the speakers. The crowd's faces are a mix of awe and suspicion. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Shot on 35mm film, anamorphic lens, shallow depth of field.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n\n```nano-banana-2\nAnchor: Chorus lines 1-2 — \"The city it was torn / A line drawn in the sand\"\nAn overhead drone shot of a crowd in an ancient city square, dramatically split down the middle. A stark, supernatural line of light acts as a divider. On one side, people turn toward the light with open hands; on the other, they turn away into deep shadow, faces hardened. Palette: high-contrast chiaroscuro, ember-and-shadow. Photorealistic, volumetric light.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n\n```nano-banana-3\nAnchor: V2 lines 1-2 — \"There is no middle ground / No place to stand aside\"\nA tight, ground-level shot focusing on the cracked cobblestones of an ancient street. In the foreground, a single, deep fissure runs directly toward the viewer, forcing the path to diverge left and right. In the blurred background, two distinct groups of people are visible on either side of the crack. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Macro detail, natural light.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n\n```nano-banana-4\nAnchor: Bridge lines 1-2 — \"You did not come for peace / Your truth, it is a sword\"\nA symbolic, abstract image. A single, ancient, unadorned iron sword stands point-down in the earth. It casts two long, opposing shadows under a dramatic sky, one stretching toward a dark, stormy horizon and the other toward a bright dawn. The sword itself glows with a faint, internal light. Palette: high-contrast chiaroscuro, ember-and-shadow. Cinematic still.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n\n```nano-banana-5\nAnchor: Outro lines 2, 4 — \"And I will choose my side\"\nA first-person perspective shot. We see only the dusty sandals of the viewer, who has just taken a definitive step across a line drawn in the dirt. The foot is planted firmly on the side where a small, determined group of people stands together, facing a rising sun. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Shot on 35mm film, golden hour.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n\n```nano-banana-title\nAnchor: The Big Idea — The proclamation of Christ is a divisive power that splits communities.\nA powerful cinematic still of a single, ancient scroll, partially unrolled on a stone floor. The scroll radiates a brilliant light that physically cracks the stone beneath it, sending a fissure spreading out into the darkness, dividing the entire frame. The image captures the immense, disruptive power of the Word. Palette: high-contrast chiaroscuro, ember-and-shadow. Volumetric light, photorealistic.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n\n```nano-banana-horizon\nAnchor: Christo-telic Horizon — The Cross is the ultimate dividing line.\nA wide, cinematic shot of three empty crosses on a hill at dawn, silhouetted against a brilliant sunrise. The central cross is slightly larger, and from its base, two distinct paths are seen winding down into the world below—one path bathed in the new light, the other still shrouded in the pre-dawn shadow. This is the ultimate division. Palette: deep indigo, starfield, volumetric blues transitioning to gold.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n",
