        "coherence_check": "## Pipeline Coherence Check\n```\nCoherence 1 — SUBJECT alignment: Exegesis Phase B Subject = Song Legend & Key gloss = Slide H1 anchor. PASS — All align on apostolic persistence after fleeing.\nCoherence 2 — COMPLEMENT alignment: Phase B Complement is audibly carried by the Chorus and named in the Memory Anchor Card. PASS — \"Persecution relocates, not stops\" is the core idea.\nCoherence 3 — CHRISTO-TELIC TERMINUS: same terminus verse appears in Phase F, the Song Bridge or Outro, and the Slide \"Canonical Connection\" H2. PASS — Rev 12:11 (Suffering Witness) is the consistent terminus.\nCoherence 4 — IMMINENCY STATUS: activated-or-not is identical across Phase G Watchman Factor, Song Bridge, cover-art `nano-banana-horizon` (which renders as Watchman's Charge when activated, Christo-telic Horizon otherwise), and Slide Watchman's Charge H2 (all fire, or none — the cover-art `horizon` slot is always emitted, only its content changes). PASS — Not activated in any module; horizon is Christo-telic.\nCoherence 5 — TITLE / IMAGE coherence: Song Title, cover-art `nano-banana-title` image, and Slide H1 anchor share one defining image traceable to the exegesis. PASS — \"Unchained Word\" / \"Seed on the wind\" all capture the theme.\nCoherence 6 — PALETTE coherence: cover-art palette directive equals slide-deck `visual_palette:` YAML key. PASS — Both specify sepia/ochre/dust-light.\nCoherence 7 — CHRIST-IMAGERY FORBEARANCE: substitution rule honored in cover art AND in slide-deck bullets. PASS — Christ is represented by the cross symbol, not depicted.\nCoherence 8 — PERICOPE alignment: every Phase A verse carries a source-named Pericope Tag; Phase 0c Pericope-Source Statement matches; Big Idea (Phase B) is stated as the pericope's; cross-references carry source-pericope tags; boundary divergences (if any) flagged and resolved. PASS — Pericope discipline is maintained.\nCoherence 9 — APPLICATION consistency: Phase G Personal-Doing imperative, Memory