. From an unseen source above, a brilliant, warm light radiates downwards, completely enveloping the cross and pushing back the oppressive darkness on all sides. The image is minimalist and powerful, focusing on the light conquering the shadow.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no depiction of a body or person.\n```\n```nano-banana-5\nAnchor: Outro — \"The blessing is increasing\"\nA reprise of the Chorus image, but the perspective has shifted. The camera is now behind the two speakers, looking out at the crowd, which has grown larger and more engaged. Several faces in the crowd are now illuminated by the light, their expressions shifting from mere curiosity to wonder and hope. The scene feels warmer and more vibrant.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures.\n```\n```nano-banana-title\nAnchor: Song Title — \"The Unchained Word\"\nA single, glowing dandelion seed is caught in a strong gust of wind, being carried over a vast, rugged, and dry landscape. The seed itself is a point of brilliant light against the sepia and ochre tones of the barren ground below. The image captures motion, resilience, and the promise of life in a new place. Cinematic still, macro lens, shallow depth of field.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-horizon\nAnchor: Christo-telic Horizon — The completed Great Commission.\nA symbolic image of the globe, seen from space. From a single point of light over Jerusalem, luminous, golden lines spread out like roots or veins, covering all the continents and nations, connecting them in a web of light. The image represents the gospel having been preached to all nations, fulfilling the mission that this small verse in Acts exemplifies.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n",
