hor: Bridge lines 1-2 — \"O Lord, Your Spirit can perceive / The trust Your own dear Word can weave\"\nAn abstract, symbolic image. From a dark, textured background, golden threads of light begin to weave together, forming a complex, beautiful pattern in the center. This represents faith being woven in a person's heart by the Word. The image is luminous and hopeful against the darkness. Cinematic still, shallow depth of field.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-5\nAnchor: Outro lines 3-4 — \"He leaped and walked and stood up tall / By faith that answered to the call\"\nA low-angle shot from behind, showing the silhouette of a man leaping into the air, his arms outstretched in joy. His previously crippled legs are now strong. The background is a dusty Lystran street, with the setting sun creating a powerful, hopeful flare. The focus is on the motion and liberation. Photorealistic, shot on 35mm film.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-title\nAnchor: The central image of the passage: Paul's discerning gaze meeting the man's receptive faith.\nA dramatic, cinematic still capturing the moment of connection. From Paul's perspective, looking down at the lame man. The man's face is filled with rapt attention and nascent hope. A tangible, almost visible line of golden light connects Paul's eyes to the man's heart, symbolizing the discernment of faith. Palette is warm sepia and gold, with deep shadows. Anamorphic lens, golden hour.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-horizon\nAnchor: The Christo-telic Horizon: The ultimate fulfillment of healing promised in Scripture.\nA breathtaking landscape of the New Jerusalem. In the foreground, a figure who was once lame is leaping like a deer on a grassy field beside the River of Life, fulfilling Isaiah 35:6. The light is supernatural, emanating from the glory of God and the Lamb. The mood is one of ultimate restoration, joy, and perfected wholeness. Palette is ethereal gold, crystal clear blues, and emerald green.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n",
