        "coherence_check": "## Pipeline Coherence Check\n```\nCoherence 1 — SUBJECT alignment: Exegesis Phase B Subject = Song Legend & Key gloss = Slide H1 anchor. PASS — All align on \"Apostolic Rejection of Deification\".\nCoherence 2 — COMPLEMENT alignment: Phase B Complement is carried by the Chorus (\"We are just men\") and Memory Anchor. PASS — Complement on redirecting glory is central.\nCoherence 3 — CHRISTO-TELIC TERMINUS: same terminus (Rev 5:13) appears in Phase F and will inform the Song Bridge. PASS — Terminus is consistent.\nCoherence 4 — IMMINENCY STATUS: not activated in this passage; no Watchman Factor, no Imminency in Song, horizon prompt is Christo-telic. PASS — Consistent non-activation.\nCoherence 5 — TITLE / IMAGE coherence: Song Title (\"Not Gods, But Men\"), cover-art, and Slide H1 share the core rejection theme. PASS — Thematic image is coherent.\nCoherence 6 — PALETTE coherence: cover-art palette (sepia/dust-light) will match slide-deck YAML key. PASS — Palette will be consistent.\nCoherence 7 — CHRIST-IMAGERY FORBEARANCE: not applicable as Christ is not directly depicted, but the principle is honored. PASS — Forbearance rule followed.\nCoherence 8 — PERICOPE alignment: Pericope (14:8-20) is defined and sourced; cross-references are tagged. PASS — Pericope discipline is maintained.\nCoherence 9 — APPLICATION consistency: Phase G, Memory Card, Devotional, and Quiz Q4 all focus on deflecting glory to God. PASS — Application is unified.\n```\n",
