        "slide_deck_sidecar": "## Slide Deck Sidecar\n```markdown\n---\nbook: \"Acts\"\nchapter: \"14\"\nsection: \"21\"\nvisual_palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre\n---\n\n# Acts 14:21 — The Apostolic Pattern: Preach, Disciple, Return\nThis single verse encapsulates the three-fold apostolic strategy for building the church: bold gospel proclamation, intentional disciple-making, and courageous pastoral consolidation.\n\n*Slide deck: 7 sections, 7 total sub-slides, ≤5 bullets per slide.*\n",
        "slide_deck_sidecar_html": "<h2>Slide Deck Sidecar</h2>\n<h2>```markdown</h2>\n<p>book: \"Acts\"\nchapter: \"14\"\nsection: \"21\"\nvisual_palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre</p>\n<hr>\n<h1>Acts 14:21 — The Apostolic Pattern: Preach, Disciple, Return</h1>\n<p>This single verse encapsulates the three-fold apostolic strategy for building the church: bold gospel proclamation, intentional disciple-making, and courageous pastoral consolidation.</p>\n<p><em>Slide deck: 7 sections, 7 total sub-slides, ≤5 bullets per slide.</em></p>",
        "cover_art_prompts": "## Cover Art Prompts\n```nano-banana-1\nAnchor: V1 lines 3-4 — \"A fragile faith on hostile ground / A whispered hope is all we found\"\nA single, small green sprout pushes up through a crack in a large, gray flagstone in a desolate city square at twilight. The lighting is low and dramatic, with long shadows. The mood is one of fragile, tenacious hope. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Cinematic still, shot on 35mm film, anamorphic lens, shallow depth of field.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-2\nAnchor: Chorus lines 3-4 — \"Then you stay to make the man / And then return to build the plan\"\nClose-up on two pairs of hands in a dimly lit room. One pair, weathered and strong, is gesturing as if teaching. The other pair, younger, is open and receiving. An architectural drawing or map is faintly visible on the table between them. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Photorealistic, shot with natural light, volumetric light shafts from a high window.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-3\nAnchor: V2 lines 1-3 — \"The stones they threw are on the road... But love requires the road back home\"\nTwo pairs of dusty, sandaled feet walking back along a rough stone road towards a city gate. The stones on the road are sharp and uneven. The perspective is low to the ground, emphasizing the difficulty of the journey. The sun is setting behind them, casting long forward shadows. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Cinematic still, golden hour.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-4\nAnchor: Bridge lines 3-4 — \"The road is hard You have bestowed / But we will walk the brave, hard road\"\nA wide, epic shot of two figures silhouetted against a vast, rugged landscape, walking on a winding dirt path that leads back towards a distant, fortified city. The sky is dramatic and filled with clouds, but a single beam of light breaks through to illuminate the path ahead. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Cinematic still, shot on 35mm film, anamorphic lens.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-5\nAnchor: Outro lines 3-4 — \"Not just a crowd, a house well built / On grace that covers all our guilt\"\nThe interior of a simple, ancient stone house, warmly lit by oil lamps. A diverse group of people—men, women, children—are gathered together, sharing a meal. The feeling is one of community, safety, and belonging. The focus is on the interlocking stones of the wall behind them. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Photorealistic, warm amber light.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-title\nAnchor: Title — \"The Road Back Home\"\nA pair of well-worn leather sandals resting on a milestone beside a dusty, ancient Roman road. The road stretches back towards a city visible in the hazy distance. The milestone has faint, unreadable carvings. The image evokes a long journey completed and a deliberate choice to return. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Cinematic still, photorealistic, shallow depth of field.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-horizon\nAnchor: Christo-telic Horizon — The Chief Shepherd's charge.\nAn abstract, symbolic image. A simple, handcrafted wooden shepherd's crook leans against a large, rough-hewn stone. In the background, out of focus, is a flock of sheep grazing on a green hill at dawn. The image represents the authority and care of the Chief Shepherd being passed to the under-shepherds. Palette: soft dawn go