is daunting but hopeful. Anamorphic lens, HDR. Palette: deep indigo and black shadows, with a brilliant line of gold and amber at the horizon.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-horizon\nAnchor: The Christo-telic horizon of the passage — the path of suffering leads to the glory secured by Christ.\nA cinematic still from inside a dark, rock-hewn tomb, looking out. The massive stone is rolled away from the entrance, and brilliant, blinding morning light is flooding in, illuminating the dust motes in the air. The rough edges of the tomb entrance frame the shot. Visible just outside is the end of the same rocky path from the other images, now bathed in glorious light. The mood is one of triumphant finality. Volumetric light. Palette: cool, dark stone in the foreground, with an explosion of warm, brilliant gold and white light.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```",
