        "slide_deck_sidecar_html": "<h2>Slide Deck Sidecar</h2>\n<h2>```markdown</h2>\n<p>book: \"Acts\"\nchapter: \"14\"\nsection: \"22\"\nvisual_palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre</p>\n<hr>\n<h1>Acts 14:22 — The Necessary Road to the Kingdom</h1>\n<p>This single verse summarizes the core of apostolic discipleship: strengthening new believers with the hard-won truth that suffering is the divinely appointed path into God's kingdom.</p>\n<p><em>Slide deck: 7 sections, 8 total sub-slides, ≤5 bullets per slide.</em></p>",
        "cover_art_prompts": "## Cover Art Prompts\n```nano-banana-1\nAnchor: V1 lines 1-2 — \"They strengthen souls to stand up straight, / To bear the burden, face the hate\"\nA cinematic still of two figures in ancient, simple robes, one with a comforting hand on the other's shoulder. They stand on a dusty road at the edge of a village, facing away from the viewer towards a rugged, ascending path. The scene is lit by the warm, golden-hour light of late afternoon, casting long shadows. Palette is sepia parchment, dust-light, and ochre. Photorealistic, shot on 35mm film, shallow depth of field.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-2\nAnchor: Chorus lines 1 & 3 — \"Through many trials we must go, / The necessary seeds we sow\"\nAn ultra-high-resolution close-up of cracked, dry earth. A single, vibrant green sprout is pushing its way up through a fissure in the ground. The lighting is dramatic chiaroscuro, with a single ray of light illuminating the sprout against the dark, hard-packed soil. The mood is one of resilient hope against overwhelming odds. Anamorphic lens, cinematic still. Palette: deep ochre and shadow, with a single point of vivid green.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-3\nAnchor: V2 lines 1-2 — \"Don't be surprised when trials press, / This world will give you nothing less\"\nA cinematic still from a low angle, looking up at a traveler's worn leather sandals taking a step onto a sharp, rocky section of an ascending path. The rocks are jagged and cast sharp shadows. The background is a blur of motion, suggesting a difficult journey. The image focuses entirely on the feet and the immediate challenge of the terrain. Volumetric light,