 counts are verified per line (6-8).\nGate 24: PASS — Title is evocative, concrete, and memorable.\n\n***\n\n```text\nTitle: The Hard Road Back\nStyle: Folk rock, male vocalist, sparse arrangement, acoustic guitar, driving rhythm, upright bass, subtle mandolin, raw analog capture, tape saturation\nDirectives: No song introduction. Abrupt start.\n\n[Verse 1]\n(A) The seed was sown on foreign ground\n(A) A new-found faith was heard\n(B) But roots need depth to hold the sound\n(B) Of your life-giving word\n\n[Chorus]\n(A) Through Pisidia's dust and stone\n(A) The hard road back is love\n(B) To strengthen souls you call your own\n(B) Sent down from high above\n\n[Verse 2]\n(A) The easy ship waits on the sea\n(A) A quick return from toil\n(B) But shepherds walk where sheep will be\n(B) On rugged, rocky soil\n\n[Chorus]\n(A) Through Pisidia's dust and stone\n(A) The hard road back is love\n(B) To strengthen souls you call your own\n(B) Sent down from high above\n\n[Bridge]\n(A) O Shepherd, you walked it first for us\n(A) The long road to the cross\n(B) So we will build your church and trust\n(B) No labor is a loss\n\n[Outro]\nThe hard road back is love\nTo strengthen every soul\nThe hard road back is love\nTo make the broken whole\n```\n",
