        "cover_art_prompts": "## Cover Art Prompts\n```nano-banana-1\nAnchor: V1 lines 1-2 — \"From Antioch we sailed away / To bring the light of day\"\nA cinematic still of an ancient Roman merchant ship leaving a bustling harbor at dawn. The light of the rising sun breaks over the horizon, catching the sail. The mood is one of hopeful departure and divine purpose. Shot on 35mm film, anamorphic lens, warm amber palette.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-2\nAnchor: Chorus lines 1-2 — \"Entrusted to the grace of God / The path the Spirit trod\"\nA symbolic, photorealistic image. A pair of worn, calloused hands are held open, cupped together. A soft, golden light emanates from within them, illuminating the hands from below. The background is a simple, dark texture, focusing all attention on the light being held and entrusted. Shallow depth of field, volumetric light.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-3\nAnchor: V2 lines 1-2 — \"We have a mission of our own / Not by our strength alone\"\nA modern, relatable scene. A person is kneeling on a wooden floor in a simply furnished room, hands folded in prayer over an open Bible and a world map. Soft morning light streams through a window, casting long shadows. The mood is one of quiet dedication and dependence. Natural light, warm amber palette.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-4\nAnchor: Bridge lines 3-4 — \"We'll give account for all we've done / Before the Risen Son\"\nA symbolic and majestic wide shot. A lone figure stands on the edge of a calm, glassy sea, looking toward a distant, brilliant throne of light that pierces through clouds. The throne itself is the source of all light in the scene, suggesting a final, awesome accountability. The mood is one of awe and reverence, not fear.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-5\nAnchor: Outro lines 1-2 — \"We sailed back to the shore / And trusted Him once more\"\nA close-up shot focusing on the weathered, wooden tiller of an ancient ship. A hand rests gently upon it, guiding it. In the background, out of focus, is the warm, welcoming sight of a harbor and city lights at dusk. The feeling is one of safe arrival and mission accomplished. Golden hour lighting.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-title\nAnchor: The central image of the passage — returning to the harbor of grace.\nAn ultra-high-resolution cinematic still of an ancient Roman ship, sails full, entering a peaceful harbor at sunset. The water reflects the warm, golden light of the sky. The city of Antioch, with its characteristic ancient architecture, is visible on the shore, lights beginning to twinkle. The mood is one of profound peace, relief, and successful completion. Photorealistic, shot on 35mm film, warm amber palette.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-horizon\nAnchor: The Christo-telic Horizon — the final report and the fruit of the mission.\nA breathtaking, symbolic panorama depicting the fulfillment of the Great Commission. Before a radiant, unseen throne, a vast, diverse multitude from every nation, tribe, and tongue (Revelation 7:9) stands in worship. Their faces are lifted in joy. The image is not of a single person, but of the corporate, global fruit of the mission that began in verses like Acts 14:26. Volumetric light, cinematic.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n",
