. Chorus: time/vine, stay/pray. Bridge: call/all, rest/blest.\nGate 22: PASS — Final output is a single fenced `text` block.\nGate 23: PASS — All lines are within the 5-9 syllable count.\nGate 24: PASS — Title is short, memorable, and from the text's key phrase.\n\n```text\nTitle: No Little Time\nStyle: Folk rock, male vocalist, gentle acoustic guitar, upright bass, subtle brushed drums, Hammond organ swells, Large room acoustics, live room bleed, thick mid-range, wooden resonance, environmental air, no noise reduction, raw analog capture, tape saturation\nDirectives: No song introduction. Abrupt start.\n\n[Verse 1]\nThe dust is on the road (A)\nThe gospel seed bestowed (A)\nNow weary feet come home (B)\nNo longer called to roam (B)\n\n[Chorus]\nFor no little time (A)\nHe tends the growing vine (A)\nHe calls us here to stay (B)\nTo gather and to pray (B)\n\n[Verse 2]\nThe roots must now go deep (A)\nThe promises to keep (A)\nThe learners must be taught (B)\nThe truth the blood has bought (B)\n\n[Chorus]\nFor no little time (A)\nHe tends the growing vine (A)\nHe calls us here to stay (B)\nTo gather and to pray (B)\n\n[Bridge]\nThe going has a call (A)\nBut staying is for all (A)\nO Lord, our final rest (B)\nIs in Your presence blest (B)\n\n[Outro]\nHe calls us here to stay\nTo gather and to pray\nFor no little time\nNo little time\n\n[End]\n```\n",
