        "slide_deck_sidecar": "## Slide Deck Sidecar\n```markdown\n---\nbook: \"Acts\"\nchapter: \"14\"\nsection: \"28\"\nvisual_palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre\n---\n\n# Acts 14:28 — The Rhythm of Mission: Staying to Strengthen\nThis single, transitional verse reveals a vital, often overlooked, aspect of the church's mission: the strategic importance of staying, teaching, and consolidating the faith of the disciples between seasons of expansion.\n\n*Slide deck: 5 sections, 5 total sub-slides, ≤5 bullets per slide.*\n",
        "slide_deck_sidecar_html": "<h2>Slide Deck Sidecar</h2>\n<h2>```markdown</h2>\n<p>book: \"Acts\"\nchapter: \"14\"\nsection: \"28\"\nvisual_palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre</p>\n<hr>\n<h1>Acts 14:28 — The Rhythm of Mission: Staying to Strengthen</h1>\n<p>This single, transitional verse reveals a vital, often overlooked, aspect of the church's mission: the strategic importance of staying, teaching, and consolidating the faith of the disciples between seasons of expansion.</p>\n<p><em>Slide deck: 5 sections, 5 total sub-slides, ≤5 bullets per slide.</em></p>",
        "cover_art_prompts": "## Cover Art Prompts\n```nano-banana-1\nAnchor: V1 lines 1, 3 — \"The dust is on the road...Now weary feet come home\"\nA cinematic still of two men in simple, travel-worn 1st-century robes, seen from behind, walking through a large stone city gate into the warm, golden-hour light of Antioch. The mood is one of weary relief and arrival. Shot on 35mm film, anamorphic lens, with visible dust motes in the air. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Negative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures.\n```\n```nano-banana-2\nAnchor: Chorus lines 3-4 — \"He calls us here to stay / To gather and to pray\"\nA cinematic still from inside a simple, lamp-lit room in ancient Antioch. A diverse group of men and women are seated on cushions, listening intently. The focus is on their engaged postures, not their faces, which are in soft focus or shadow. Light from a central oil lamp creates a warm, intimate atmosphere. Shallow depth of field. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Negative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces.\n```\n```nano-banana-3\nAnchor: V2 lines 3-4 — \"The learners must be taught / The truth the blood has bought\"\nA close-up cinematic still of weathered hands carefully unrolling an ancient Hebrew scroll on a simple wooden table. The room is filled with soft, directional light as if from a nearby window, illuminating the textures of the parchment and the wood. The image conveys deep study and the transmission of sacred truth. Photorealistic detail. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Negative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-4\nAnchor: Bridge lines 3-4 — \"O Lord, our final rest / Is in Your presence blest\"\nA symbolic, cinematic still looking up from a dimly lit, ancient courtyard towards a sky where brilliant, heavenly light breaks through dark clouds. The architecture is earthly, but the light is otherworldly, suggesting the promise of our eternal home and God's dwelling place. Volumetric light rays pierce the darkness. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre, with a piercing gold/white light. Negative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-5\nAnchor: Outro lines 1-2 — \"He calls us here to stay / To gather and to pray\"\nA cinematic still, a wider shot of the same lamp-lit room from the Chorus prompt. The camera is pulled back, showing the community as a whole, bound together in fellowship. The atmosphere is peaceful, stable, and deeply rooted. The warmth of the community is the central subject. Natural light mixed with lamplight. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Negative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces.\n```\n```nano-banana-title\nAnchor: Song Title — \"No Little Time\"\nThe definitive image from the Chorus: a cinematic still focusing on a single, beautifully crafted clay oil lamp burning brightly on a rustic wooden table. Around it, the blurred, warm shapes of people gathered in fellowship create a strong sense of community and stability. The focus is on the steady, enduring flame. Shallow depth of field, shot on 35mm film. Palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre. Negative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-horizon\nAnchor: Christo-telic Horizon — The eternal dwelling of God with His people.\nA symbolic and majestic cinematic still. From a vantage point on a hill, we look across a valley towards a magnificent, glowing city that is clearly not of this world—the New Jerusalem. The architecture is ancient but perfect, bathed in a light that seems to emanate from the city itself, not the sun. This is the ultimate \"homecoming\" and \"staying.\" Palette: deep indigo, starfield, with a city of brilliant gold and pearl. Negative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n",
